# Project: Personal Brand Monorepo
# Stack: Yarn 4 workspaces + Turborepo, vanilla JS, CSS custom properties, static HTML

## Project Structure
- `packages/design-system/` — Shared CSS design system (@vnyson/design-system), published to npm
  - `css/tokens.css` — Design tokens (colors, spacing, typography, etc.)
  - `css/base.css` — Reset and global styles (@layer base)
  - `css/components.css` — Reusable component styles (@layer components)
- `sites/<site-name>/` — Individual static sites
  - Each site has its own `package.json`, `index.html`, `css/`, `js/`
  - Sites consume `@vnyson/design-system` via workspace dependency
  - JS is bundled with esbuild (`js/main.js` → `js/bundle.js`)

## Coding Conventions

### General
- 2-space indentation, single quotes, trailing commas, LF line endings
- UTF-8 charset, insert final newline in all files
- Use `const` by default, `let` only when reassignment is needed, never `var`
- Prefer early returns over deep nesting
- No hardcoded magic numbers — use named constants or CSS custom properties

### CSS
- Always use design tokens from `tokens.css` — never hardcode colors, spacing, font sizes, or radii
- Use `@layer base` for resets, `@layer components` for component styles
- New tokens go in `tokens.css`, new components go in `components.css`
- Use CSS custom properties for all values that may vary or be themed
- Mobile-first responsive design — use `min-width` media queries
- Class naming: lowercase, hyphenated (e.g., `.section-divider`, `.heading-xl`)

### JavaScript
- ES modules only (`import`/`export`)
- Always check for DOM element existence before operating on it (null guards)
- Respect `prefers-reduced-motion` for all animations and interactive effects
- Use event delegation where practical
- Keep functions small and single-purpose

### HTML
- Always include `<!DOCTYPE html>`, `lang` attribute, viewport meta, and `<title>`
- All `<img>` elements must have `alt` attributes
- No inline styles — use CSS classes
- Use semantic elements (`<main>`, `<section>`, `<nav>`, etc.)

## Commands
- `yarn lint` — Run all linters (ESLint, Stylelint, HTMLHint)
- `yarn lint:css` — Run Stylelint only
- `yarn lint:html` — Run HTMLHint only
- `yarn format` — Auto-format all files with Prettier
- `yarn format:check` — Check formatting without writing
- `yarn build` — Build all workspaces via Turbo
- `yarn dev` — Start dev servers

## Commit Messages
- Use Conventional Commits: `type(scope): description`
- Types: feat, fix, docs, style, refactor, perf, test, chore, build, ci
- Examples: `feat(tennis-stringing): add pricing section`, `fix(design-system): correct token spacing scale`

## Before Considering Work Done
1. Run `yarn format:check` — no formatting issues
2. Run `yarn lint` — no errors (warnings are acceptable but should be noted)
3. Run `yarn build` — all workspaces build successfully
4. Test in browser — visual and interactive behavior is correct

## Adding a New Site
1. Create `sites/<site-name>/` with `package.json`, `index.html`, `css/`, `js/`
2. Add `"@vnyson/design-system": "workspace:*"` dependency
3. Add lint/build scripts matching existing site conventions
4. Import design system CSS: `@import '../../../packages/design-system/css/tokens.css'`
